                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> While I admit having some drop spells is nice, this is ridiculus. Having the best spells a little more difficult to obtain is great and all, but when all of them are like that doesnt that also make it feel like nothing. Zaar, you say there was no excitment getting your spells, well is there much excitement in wathcing a spectral drop and thinking "oh great I get a root". <br /><br />The whole concept behind drop spells I actually like. However, not every spell is a great idea for a drop spell. Some spells just suck. No 2 ways about it. I beleive there should be more purchasable spells. Nothing spectacular like the new lich or the rogue pet. Those are way to big of an upgrade to just hand out like that. But look at the new sheilding spells. Do they really need to be a drop spell? <br /><br />VI for some reason thought this would be the best thing ever. I couldnt disagree more. They destroyed the concept of making spells drop. The drop spells are (normally) some of the best spells you can hope for at your lvl. But now so are the crap ones. I agree you shouldnt be handed your spell book just for lvling, but you shouldnt have to bust your ass for crap spells. There is a happy medium to all this, I just wish VI would implememnet it.<br /><br />Sell us a few of our spells that arent huge upgrades. The sheilding line and the roots jump out at me for these spells. Rune of death is also one of those things that really isnt that much of a differance. None of these spells are overpowering, and you will need drops for all of the better spells still. Too bad it will never happen.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
