                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> As a few other people have mentioned, attack VI not Triton. Triton was not responsible for programming anything in the game, VI was. So stop taking out your anger at Triton.<br /><br />Anyone who's played EQ for more than a year should know that VI always releases zones which either give too much xp or have too high drop rates or both, only to nerf them about a month later. In the case of The Grey, the nerfings continued right up till a few months before PoP was released.<br /><br />The early bird catches the worm. This is true in RL and in EQ. Don't blame the bird that managed to get in before you.<br /><br />The thing to remember about the new spells though is that they aren't exactly anything new to people who've had Funeral Pyre for months. None of them are upgrades to FP so they don't exactly have a WOW factor there. However, for the rest of us plebs who are still dreaming of scribing FP, each one of these new dots are seriously important upgrades. So on one hand we have the ubers with FP and a bunch of 63+ spells which, while nice to have, aren't great upgrades. On the other hand we have the rest of us who don't have FP or a bunch of 63+ spells which would be amazing upgrades. The dividing line between the 2 groups of necros became wider when PoP was released but then became even wider when the spectral drop rate got nerfed after the ubers got their spells.<br /><br />I would probably agree that the initial spectral drop rates were too high, but this is all based on what I've heard not experienced for myself. I'd expected to see a sharp decrease in drop rates, but the current rates seem totally out of whack. Essentially, when uberguild casters have to discuss/argue/fight over scraps of parchment, you know that there must be something very wrong going on.<br /><br />None of us deserve to have all our spells handed to us. However, we deserve to have a reasonable chance to get those spells if we work to get them. Currently, there is a lot of hard work being put in with sparse rewards to show.<br /><br />Tenaiya Soulscorcher</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
