                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Great post.  I hope that you clean it up some and send it every day to verant and/or submit it via the station.  I would and it needs to be done.<br /><br />As for the spell situation, well it pisses me off to be sure and its killed my desire to play the game.<br /><br />Essentially what has happened is they have changed the way spells come into the game and the way they function towards class balance.  Spells are like rare gear now, instead of something that is almost an ability you get upon level up like they were pre-Kunark.<br /><br />This started happening significantly with certain Luclin spells and it different for different classes, which was another mistake of Verant's.  Imagine being a wiz and having to be in an Emperor capable guild to get GSS.  Talk about an ass fuck.  Truth be told, this all started to happen with Kunark.  When Verant abandoned research, another mistake, and put 1/2 spells onto drop tables and made certain ones rarer than others.<br /><br />But Kunark wasnt as bad as the current situation.<br /><br />For one thing, there were spells on vendors for almost each level.  In some cases these vendor spells were damn good.  Deflux, Vexing and Pyrocruor were awesome spells at the time.  Fast forward to PoP and we get...Dark Plague.  Each class gets one 61+ spell. perhaps 5% of their total new 61+ spells as opposed to the ~50% on Vendors with Kunark.  Thats a big difference, like %1000 percent.<br /><br />In Kunark the harder to get spells were not restricted by character flags or guild membership.  Yes the crypt was camped a lot but with a strong group you could get in and camp Chottal.  In some funny foreshadowing kind of way before Chottal was nerfed we has like HoH before it was nerfed.  He dropped tons of spells.  Outside of Chottal you had Kunark dragons that also dropped 59-60 spells.  They were hard for a while but if your guild couldnt take them they could almost certainly successfully 'raid' skyfire to hunt GWs which dropped spells about 25% of the time and were almost never camped.  Fast forward to PoP.  The lowest tier of spells, 61/62 are more rare than the 51-54s were in Kunark, and thats saying a lot.  But it gets worse, much worse, as you go up.  63/64 spells are uber rare if you didnt ride the HoH gravy train or benefit from friends/guildmates that did.  And then to top it off, no 65 spells for people not in the top 1-2 guilds.  None.<br /><br />The bottomline is I dont see a way that anyone could be happy with the way spells work in PoP unless a) they dont play the game or a caster or b) they are in the best guild on their server (Zaar) and benefitted from pre-nerf HoH and whatever single group glyphed rune camp there was. As well as access to higher level zones not being a problem.<br /><br />Spells have changed for the worse IMO.  They are no longer 1/2 way between a class ability and gear but are firmly entrenched in the gear side of the equation.  Thats what we are seeing with spells and its a new development with the FOURTH expansion.  A little late for such a fundamental change if you ask me.<br /><br />Sayleth<br /><br /><br /><br />And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
